      },
      "lineNbr": 117,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-27T03:25:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "do we want the generic (\u003dless useful) git-diff or a more concrete (\u003dmore useful) git-log that would give us a blamelist?\nnote that strictly speaking git-diff would work even for different repos and for two commits where neither of commits is a ancestor of another, b/c git-diff just diffs two trees.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 117,
        "startChar": 29,
        "endLine": 117,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "1380f894a3d9f317ed84054ea4ac9c52bd49893b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7e4c8f4f_5f17878c",
        "filename": "common/proto/milo/diff.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 117,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-27T04:12:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "let me correct myself: git-diff is not more generic than git-log, or vice versa. None of them is a special case of another. They are just different. FWIU our end goal is a path from one commit to another.",
      "parentUuid": "cdba2cd4_42b9f265",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 117,
        "startChar": 29,
        "endLine": 117,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "1380f894a3d9f317ed84054ea4ac9c52bd49893b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9ff76d74_89580145",
        "filename": "common/proto/milo/diff.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 117,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-27T20:19:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There are two stages to diff computation. One is pure-data and calculates these status values. The second stage actually fetches history from gitiles. The second stage is optional.\n\n`git diff` and `git log` are functionally the same under the hood. I use \u0027git diff\u0027 here as a shorthand for both, since if you can do one, you can do the other.",
      "parentUuid": "7e4c8f4f_5f17878c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 117,
        "startChar": 29,
        "endLine": 117,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "1380f894a3d9f317ed84054ea4ac9c52bd49893b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "692b0edf_ee232b36",
        "filename": "common/proto/milo/diff.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 118,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-27T03:25:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "is this the only case when we use DIFF?\nI feel like DIFF is a premature abstraction. IMO we should design abstractions when \n1) we have at least two clear cases\n2) we need to write code that must work for both but at the same time does not have to understand specifics of each case\nHere we have \n1) one case: git\n2) the code that would use DIFF (git log/diff) has to understand git concepts anyway. It can just check that repo url is the same",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 118,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 118,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "1380f894a3d9f317ed84054ea4ac9c52bd49893b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
