      "writtenOn": "2017-09-27T03:25:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "what defines a manifest older than another one? I am not sure there is total chronologic order for manifests.\nAlso the diffing algorithm does not seem to assume/require the order to be the time order.\nWDYT about calling all the \"new\" parameters \"other\"?\n\nIf we need that for computing git history\n1) looks like this is not Diff\u0027s job to do that\n2) different repos may have different \"order\", e.g. given manifests M1 and M2 and repos R1 and R2, commit(M1, R1) may be before commit(M2, R1) and commit(M1, R2) may be after (M2, R2)",
