      "writtenOn": "2017-09-27T20:19:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "discussed offline\n  * correct, Diff\u0027s job is to extract the maximum amount of useful information given just the two Manifest\u0027s themselves. Other layers will supply history/compute diffs.\n  * yes, this isn\u0027t generally solvable, but I think that we\u0027ll have a \u0027good enough\u0027 solution in the form of order-by-console-order.\n  * since all of the raw data is available in the manifests themselves, exotic use cases can compute the diff in some other manner if needed.\n  * it may be worth adding a REVERSE_DIFF status and commit positions, then trying to order individual checkouts based on commit positions. This gets hard though.",
